NDA_Structure_Name: Alcohol and Drug Use Disorders Identification Test

NDA_Structure_Name: Alcohol and Drug Use Disorders Identification Test

NDA_Structure_Name: Alcohol and Drug Use Disorders Identification Test

NDA_Structure_Name: Alcohol and Drug Use Disorders Identification Test

FITBIR_Form_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS)
NDA_Name: 1) On how many days in the last 3 months did you miss work or school because of your headaches?
FITBIR_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) - miss work school days 3 month number
FITBIR_Description: Number of days in the last three months the participant/subject has missed work or school because of their headaches, as part of the Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) Test form.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS)
NDA_Name: 2) How many days in the last 3 months was your productivity at work or school reduced by half or more because of your headaches? (Do not include days you counted in question 1 where you missed work or school.)
FITBIR_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) - half work school days 3 months day number
FITBIR_Description: Number of days in the last three months the participant/subject has experienced productivity reduction by half or more while at work or school because of their headaches, as part of the Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) Test form.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS)
NDA_Name: 3) On how many days in the last 3 months did you not do household work because of your headaches?
FITBIR_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) - not household work days 3 months number
FITBIR_Description: Number of days in the last three months the participant/subject has not done household work because of their headaches, as part of the Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) Test form.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS)
NDA_Name: 4) How many days in the last 3 months was your productivity in household work reduced by half or more because of your headaches? (Do not include days you counted in question 3 where you did not do household work.)
FITBIR_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) - half household work 3 months day number
FITBIR_Description: Number of days in the last three months the participant/subject has experienced productivity reduction by half or more while doing household work because of their headaches, as part of the Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) Test form.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS)
NDA_Name: 5) On how many days in the last 3 months did you miss family social or leisure activities because of your headaches?
FITBIR_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) - miss activities days 3 months number
FITBIR_Description: Number of days in the last three months the participant/subject has missed family, social, or leisure activities because of their headaches, as part of the Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) Test form.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS)
NDA_Name: A) On how many days in the last 3 months did you have any headache? (If a headache lasted more than one day count each day.)
FITBIR_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) - headache days 3 months count
FITBIR_Description: Count the total number of days in the past three months the participant/subject had headache, as part of the Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) Test form.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS)
NDA_Name: B) On a scale of 0 - 10 on average how painful were these headaches?
FITBIR_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) - headache scale
FITBIR_Description: Average pain scale of the headache experienced by the participant/subject, as part of the Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) Test form.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS)
FITBIR_Name: Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) - total days with headache/migraine 3 months number
FITBIR_Description: The total number of days in the past three months the participant/subject had those activity change due to headache, as part of the Migraine Disability Assessment (MIDAS) Test form. Also used as a MIDAS score.

NDA_Name: 1b. Did you intend to die as a result of any accident?
FITBIR_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS) - Intend to die indicator.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)
NDA_Name: 2. Over your lifetime, how seriously did you think that you would be better off dead or wish you were dead?

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)
NDA_Name: 6. Over your lifetime, how seriously did you intend to act on thoughts of killing yourself?
FITBIR_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS) - Intend to act on thought of killing self seriously in mind scale.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)
NDA_Name: 7. Over your lifetime, how seriously did you intend to die as a result of a suicidal act?

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)
NDA_Name: 8. Over your lifetime, how seriously did you take active steps to prepare for a suicide attempt in which you expected or intended to die (This includes times when you were going to kill yourself, but were interrupted or stopped yourself, before harming yourself)?

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)
NDA_Name: 9. Over your lifetime, how seriously did you injure yourself on purpose without intending to kill yourself?

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)
FITBIR_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS) - Times subject Injured self on purpose without intending to kill self number.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)
NDA_Name: 10. Over your lifetime, how seriously did you attempt suicide ("A suicide attempt is a potentially self-injurious behavior, with at least some intent (>0) to die as a result or if intent can be inferred, e.g. if it is clearly not an accident or the individual thinks the act could be lethal, even though denying intent")?

FITBIR_Form_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS)
FITBIR_Name: Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS) - Total score.
FITBIR_Description: Total score, as part of Sheehan-Suicidality Tracking Scale (S-STS).

FITBIR_Form_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory - (TIPI)
FITBIR_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory (TIPI) - Extraversion score
FITBIR_Description: The score for the subject's extraversion is calculated by adding the score for item number 1 (Extraverted or enthusiastic) to the quantity of 8 minus the score for item number 6 (Reserved or quiet), then dividing that sum by 2.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory - (TIPI)
FITBIR_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory (TIPI) - Agreeableness score
FITBIR_Description: The score for the subject's agreeable is calculated by adding the score for item number 7 (Sympathetic or warm) to the quantity of 8 minus the score for item number 2 (Critical or quarrelsome), then dividing that sum by 2.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory - (TIPI)
FITBIR_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory (TIPI) - Emotional stability score
FITBIR_Description: The score for the subject's emotional stability is calculated by adding the score for item number 9 (Calm or emotionally stable) to the quantity of 8 minus the score for item number 4 (Anxious or easily upset), then dividing that sum by 2.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory - (TIPI)
FITBIR_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory (TIPI) - Conscientiousness score
FITBIR_Description: The score for the subject's conscientiousness is calculated by adding the score for item number 3 (Dependable or self-disciplined) to the quantity of 8 minus the score for item number 8 (Disorganized or careless), then dividing that sum by 2.

FITBIR_Form_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory - (TIPI)
FITBIR_Name: Ten-Item Personality Inventory (TIPI) - Openness to experience score
FITBIR_Description: The score for the subject's openness to experience is calculated by adding the score for item number 5 to the quantity of 8 minus the score for item number 10, then dividing that sum by 2, as a part of the Ten-Item Personality Inventory (TIPI).

FITBIR_Form_Name: Tinnitus Functional Index
